        public FlowSource createSource​(SourceSinkType type,
                               int parameterIdx,
                               AccessPath accessPath,
                               GapDefinition gap)
        Creates a new source model based on the given information
        Parameters:
        type - The type of data flow source
        parameterIdx - The index of the method parameter through which the source value was obtained
        accessPath - The access path describing the exact source object
        gap - The gap from which this flow originated. Null if this flow did not originate from a gap.
        Returns:
        The newly created source object

      • createGapBaseObjectSink

        public FlowSink createGapBaseObjectSink​(GapDefinition gap,
                                        soot.Type baseType)
        Creates a sink that models the base object of a call to a gap method. This is used to identify the object on which the gap method is invoked, so no access path is needed.
        Parameters:
        gap - The gap in whose base object the flow ends
        Returns:
        The sink object
